        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 7:05PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 704 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Washburn, or 12 miles east of Amarillo, moving northwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Claude, Washburn, Goodnight, and Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
